OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a largely dry start with
OL,6,Fsunny periods, cloud will bubble up to
OL,7,Fgive a somewhat cloudier afternoon. An
OL,8,Fisolated shower is possible but most
OL,9,Fplaces staying dry. Feeling cooler
OL,10,Fthan of late in the light breeze.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA bit more cloud developing
OL,13,Fin the west which can lead to the odd
OL,14,Fshower but most easing by dawn. Chilly
OL,15,Fin the north where a patchy frost will
OL,16,Fform.
OL,17,
OL,18,CThursday:FA mostly dry start to the
OL,19,Fday but more cloud developing through
OL,20,Fthe morning which will develop into
OL,21,Ffurther showers into the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
